2.00	Joseph_Beltrami	Joseph Beltrami	Joseph Beltrami is a leading Scottish lawyer. Born in Rutherglen, the son of a Italian father and Scottish mother, Beltrami was brought up in Glasgow and educated at St. Aloysius College and the University of Glasgow. He has three sons by the names of Edwin, Adrian and Jason, who have all followed in their father's footsteps. Edwin is the Chief Prosecutor of Wales, Adrian is one of London's leading Banking QCs and Jason is a Glasgow Criminal lawyer. Joseph Beltrami has appeared in over 500 murder trials, gaining a reputation as one of the most skilled and sharp-witted Scottish criminal defence lawyers of recent times. He is now enjoying retirement with his eight grand-children.	
